nglish elements across geographical distances. Tapping into current debates about colonial legacies and decolonization, as well as ongoing concerns about democracy, regional power and globalisation, this book explores a range of fresh evidence to discuss language variation across the globe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEcolinguistics. 0aEnglish languagexVariationzEnglish-speaking countries. 0aEnglish languagexVariation. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAhrens, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBallard, Elaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernaisch, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiewer, Carolin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirchfield, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurke, Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurridge, Kate, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBurridge, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuschfeld, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCharters, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGötz, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHedegard, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHess, Dominique B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIsingoma, Bebwa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKorhonen, Minna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKotze, Haidee, econtributor.4ctb4https